The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for grade classification in tissue micro-arrays (TMA) using graph convolutional networks (GCNs). The method involves modeling the spatial organization of cells as a graph and learning the morphometry of each cell using a self-supervised approach. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of graph convolutional networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories.
